Meaning of the Codes
A = Added (untracked file added)
â†’ The file git_basic.json exists in your working directory but was not in the index/commit history of the branch you checked out.
Git is telling you: "I had to add this untracked file into the working tree."
M = Modified
â†’ The file learn.js is present in both branches, but its content was modified in your working directory compared to the commit you checked out.
Git is letting you know it merged in the modification instead of discarding it.





